  "prompt": "Whose side is ISIS on in Syria, and whose side are the Kurds and Al Qaeda on in Syria?",
  "response": "In the complex conflict in Syria, various factions have distinct alliances and objectives.\n\n**ISIS (Islamic State of Iraq and Syria):** ISIS operates primarily as an extremist jihadist group and has sought to establish a caliphate in the territory it controls. It has been primarily opposed to both the Syrian government and other rebel groups, including the Kurds. ISIS has engaged in violent conflict against a wide range of actors, including the Syrian regime, the Syrian Democratic Forces (SDF) which are predominantly Kurdish, and other groups in the opposition.\n\n**Kurds:** The Kurdish forces in Syria, primarily the Syrian Democratic Forces (SDF), have been primarily aligned with the U.S. and have fought against both ISIS and the Syrian government. The SDF has played a significant role in the fight against ISIS, receiving support from the U.S. and its allies. The Kurds aim to establish a degree of autonomy in northern Syria, but their relationship with the Syrian government remains complicated.\n\n**Al-Qaeda:** Al-Qaeda's presence in Syria is mainly represented by the group Hay'at Tahrir al-Sham (HTS), which has distanced itself from the main opposition coalition and has its own set of goals. While HTS has fought against the Syrian government and has been involved in battles against ISIS, it also has a complex relationship with other Islamist factions. Al-Qaeda's interests generally align against the Syrian government and in opposition to secular and Kurdish forces.\n\nIn summary:\n- **ISIS** is primarily opposed to both the Syrian government and the SDF/Kurds.\n- **Kurds** (SDF) are aligned with the U.S. against ISIS and have a complicated relationship with the Syrian government.\n- **Al-Qaeda** (through HTS) fights against the Syrian government and ISIS, but has a distinct agenda that may differ from other opposition groups. \n\nThe dynamics are fluid, and alliances can shift based on changing circumstances on the ground.",
